This article is a transcript of a briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on March 22, 2010. In the briefing, Gibbs discusses the passage of the health care reform bill and its implications. He talks about the President's focus on economic recovery and job creation, as well as the benefits of the health care reform bill for small businesses, families, and seniors. Gibbs also addresses questions about legal challenges to the legislation, the President's upcoming meeting with Prime Minister Netanyahu, and other issues on the President's agenda. Overall, the briefing emphasizes the President's commitment to achieving his policy goals and his belief in the lasting impact of the health care reform bill.